============================================================
Step 5: Physical interpretation of generators
============================================================
  Each generator is a direction in log-Pi space along which
  the friction factor f is preserved: simultaneously rescale
  Re_p, phi and (1-phi) along g and the flow stays invariant
  (the local Ergun regime is preserved).

  Generator 1:
    Re_p x exp(-0.088*eps), phi x exp(+0.992*eps), 1-phi x exp(+0.087*eps)
    Meaning: increase phi while decrease Re_p, increase 1-phi
             to keep friction factor f invariant

  Generator 2:
    Re_p x exp(+0.996*eps), phi x exp(+0.087*eps)
    Meaning: increase Re_p while increase phi
             to keep friction factor f invariant


